  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-04-21",
    "date": "2004-05-04T14:25:21Z",
    "text": "Provides reimbursement for members of the Armed Forces who are retired for a combat-related disability for travel, during the two-year period beginning on the date of such retirement, to a military treatment facility for medical care. Requires such reimbursement to be under the same terms and conditions, and at the same rate, that applies to beneficiary travel reimbursement provided by the Secretary of Veterans Affairs."
